readability_reflection: Concatenation, but I think it's because the CompSci program I've taken in my university does not teach interpolation in its I or II introductory courses, so I was less familiar.
comprehension_debugging: At the end of the day, it's code so there was no way I was going to get thought it quickly, but I'll say the interpolation threw me off at times because I didn't know how it worked.
preference_rationale: For the factors mentioned above, concatenation. It also seems cleaner to me but I'm heavily biased.
learning_curve: I was unfamiliar with interpolation and I had to catch on on its function so it delayed my ability by some factor.
suggestions_improvement: Cohesion. If possible have the same syntax in a short block of code.
